# Perth Glory News Project Rules

## Project Structure
- Use SvelteKit with TypeScript
- Deploy on Vercel
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- MongoDB for data storage

## Key Directories
- `/src/lib`: Shared utilities and components
- `/src/routes`: SvelteKit routes and API endpoints
- `/src/components`: Reusable Svelte components
- `/static`: Static assets

## Coding Standards
- Use TypeScript for all .ts/.svelte files
- Follow SvelteKit conventions for routing
- Implement proper error handling
- Use async/await for asynchronous operations
- Document complex functions with JSDoc

## Performance Guidelines
- Implement proper caching strategies
- Optimize images and media assets
- Use lazy loading where appropriate
- Keep bundle sizes minimal

## Development Workflow
1. Run `npm install` to install dependencies
2. Use `npm run dev` for local development
3. Run `npm run build` before deployment
4. Use `npm run preview` to test production build
